cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the characterization of networking in various regions of major Cloud platforms, including latency and throughput measurements, as well as an analysis of the costs involved with Cloud-based networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the importance of data movement in scientific computing production campaigns, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper provides a qualitative analysis of the results, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity and Cryptography) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper includes an analysis of the costs involved with Cloud-based networking, which could also place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
